    "AI-Reliant Code Generator & Refiners accounted for 21.92%, while AI-Assisted Code Refiners (8.22%), AI-Reliant Code Generators (11.64%), and AI-Independent Coders (6.85%) were less prevalent.",
    "To identify the changes in students' AI interaction profiles across three sessions, the McNemar-Bowker tests were conducted.",
    "The results showed significant differences between Session 1 and Session 2 (χ² (10, N = 135) = 34.478, p <.001), and Session 2 and Session 3 (χ² (10, N = 136) = 57.099, p <.001).",
    "Table 2 Students' AI interaction profiles based on their prompting behavior Interaction Profile 1st Session (N = 146) 2nd Session (N = 146) 3rd Session (N = 146) Profile Explanation AI-Reliant Code Generator 45 (30.82%) 32 (21.92%) 17 (11.64%) Students who directly paste the entire or partial programming task instructions and aim for quick, direct answers from ChatGPT without much engagement in the problemsolving process.",
    "AI-Reliant Code Generator & Refiner 15 (10.27%) 46 (31.51%) 32 (21.92%) Students who first directly paste the entire or partial programming task instructions to get a direct answer from ChatGPT."
